 Editor's note: This article is updated each time new information becomes available.JOHANNESBURG - Anglo American has agreed to sell its Eskom-linked coal-mines for R2.3-billion.The mines will be taken over by Seriti Resources.The black-owned company is set to become the second-largest supplier of coal to Eskom once the deal is concluded.The move was prompted by Eskom s demand for more coal to be supplied by majority black-owned companies.This is also part of Anglo s strategy to dispose of assets in order to reduce debt.The power utility currently generates more than 90-percent of its electricity from the burning of coal.Reuters